---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Learn how Urban Harvest Lab approaches urban gardening advice and product recommendations for small-space growers."
  canonicalPath="/about/"
>
  <section class="page-section">
    <div class="container page-hero">
      <div class="page-hero__panel">
        <span class="eyebrow">About Urban Harvest Lab</span>
        <h1>Helpful growing advice for people working with small spaces.</h1>
        <p>
          Urban Harvest Lab exists to make small-space gardening feel less confusing. The aim is to explain what
          matters, skip the fluff, and help readers make decisions they can actually use at home.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="container info-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="eyebrow">Editorial mission</span>
        <h2>What the site aims to do</h2>
        <p>
          Publish practical, evidence-based guides that help people grow food in compact spaces without relying on
          trends, jargon, or unnecessary gear.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <span class="eyebrow">Audience</span>
        <h2>Who the content serves</h2>
        <p>
          Apartment dwellers, balcony gardeners, indoor herb growers, beginner hydroponic users, and anyone who wants
          clearer context before spending money or changing a setup.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <span class="eyebrow">Editorial standard</span>
        <h2>How recommendations are made</h2>
        <p>
          When a product is recommended, the goal is to explain who it suits, where it helps, and when it is probably
          not worth the money. Sometimes the best advice is to use what you already have or skip the purchase
          altogether.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <span class="eyebrow">Publishing model</span>
        <h2>Built to grow over time</h2>
        <p>
          The site mixes broad beginner guides with deeper follow-up articles so readers can start simple and keep
          learning without having to relearn the basics from scratch.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
